<Author>HoustonSoccerMamaMD
<Content>NOLA is back! Good hotel,Great location. Just back from a fabulous long weekend in New Orleans. If you are at all unsure if you should go back to the Big Easy - DO IT!!The French Quarter is basically the same - lively, funky, wierd, historical, charming.... perhaps a bit less crowded and with more for rent/lease signs up, but otherwise unscathed.Uptown  Garden District  Magazine Street were amazingly alive  well!! Restaurants  shops on Magazine were buzzing.St. Charles Streetcar still not up  running, but perhaps in '07.Commanders' food was as good as ever, though the service was noticeably younger  less experienced. New decor downstairs is good  bad (love the birds/wallpaper but the corner pavillions??) Cafe Du Monde, Acme, Columns, Pat O's, Preservation Hall, Laffite's, Central Grocery, Galatoire's, etc etc are all up  running  as good as ever. Who knew I'd ever be excited to see those high-heeled legs bobbing in  out of the wall on Bourbon? That's right, they're back too!Th Bourbon Orleans hotel is in a GREAT location - just behind the Cathedral, around the corner from Rodrigue's gallery  just off Bourbon. If you want quiet, ask for a room closer to Royal. We had a 3rd floor loft room with a fantastic balcony. The lobby is beautiful, the concierge so helpful  very New Orleanian, and the staff was VERY friendly. The elevators, hallways,  rooms could use a little TLC but just a little would go a long way (chipped/scratched wood/paint on some doors etc) . The courtyard  pool looked beautiful  clean and hygiene was ABSOLUTELY not an issue/problem. The one true complait I have is not related to this Hotel, but to Wyndam: Why have a ridiculously overpriced Herman Miller desk chair when the sofa is the single most uncomfortable sofa I have ever sat on??? And that includes college...??? Half the $$ it took to get the business chair would have been MUCH better spent on a higher quality sofa for the room- particularly in a place like the French Quarter.NOTE: You only get the benefit of the Wyndham Rewards Program if you reserve directly thru Wyndham.The people in the Quarter  in New Orleans in general were friendlier than EVER. They know what people think of the city  are struggling to regain some dignity and the confidence of the travelling public. We had a WONDERFUL, safe, fun, interesting, reassuring, magical, delicious, historical, decadent  spiritual visit. And all that in just 2 days...only in New Orleans, today  forever.All in all, I say LAISSEZ LES BONS TEMPS ROULEZ and visit New Orleans!! You'll be glad you did. 
