<Author>uptownnolagirl
<Content>Could be really good! As New Orleaneans, we have always recommended the Windsor Court to people looking for a special stay in the city. However, we moved last summer, and the reviews on tripadvisor post-Katrina for the Windsor Court were not all good. We decided to try the Bourbon Orleans. It's a beautiful hotel in a great location. Per the adivce of another tripadvisor member, we signed up for the Wyndham rewards program to get free drinks on arrival, snacks, and free valet parking. All of the above were forgotten during our stay! The rooms are fine - a little small. If you want quiet, ask for a room far away from Bourbon. We asked to make sure that we weren't on Bourbon, and they put us in a corner room or Bourbon and St. Ane. It was really loud. I believe fully that New Orleans is a city for families - but I don't know if this hotel is. I don't even know if it's for serious travellers. A parade of drunks woke us up each night from 3-5 AM as they returned to their rooms. One night, a guy banged on our door door demanding his friends. Ten minutes later, he pulled the fire alarm. What was most alarming about this was that he also sprayed the extinguisher, and the hallway appeared to be filled with smoke when we opened our doors. The drunk man ran wild in the lobby, as the guests waited there for the go-ahead to return to their rooms. No arrests were made, as the management informed the guests that tourists were not currently being arrested in the city. Huh? Anyhow - our sleep was interrupted each night by rowdy guests. Guests should also know that there is very limited room service. You can basically order up a cheeseburger or a turkey sandwich...but why would you even want that when the Royal Street Grocery is a block away serving up soft-shell crab po-boys and snoballs, too! The hotel has a beautiful lobby, and a nice garden pool. If the management could figure out a way to sit on it's rowdy guests - this would be a great place for anyone to stay in the quarter. 
