<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Noisy but Nice I stayed at the Wyndham Bourbon Orleans Hotel when attending a two-day intense work related seminar held at the hotel. I took my family with me and we stayed an additional couple days as a mini-vacation. Our flight was scheduled to arrive in New Orleans at around 10 p.m. so I made a call to the hotel before leaving for the airport to let them know we would be arriving late but that we would definitely be there. They assured me that my reservation was secure and that they just didn't give reserved rooms away. When we arrived at nearly 11 p.m. they had given our room away and told us there was nothing available. They eventually found something for us but it was an upgrade and only for one night--we had to move rooms in the morning. They assured us our room would be available the next day. It wasn't. They were telling us we would need to find another hotel but again, they eventually found us a room we were able to stay in the rest of our stay. The front desk staff were rude and didn't seem to care a hoot about the fact we'd made reservations several months in advance... not enjoyable people by any means, but aside from that, we found the rooms clean and attractive. We loved the watercolor lithographs on the walls of our room and enjoyed the wonderful scent of the soaps and lotions provided. Maid service was extremely friendly and very enjoyable. The bellboys were extremely helpful in giving us restaurant tips and walking directions and scheduling taxis for us--they also had fantastic senses of humor and were very fun. The hotel restaurant provided the luncheon for both days of the seminar and made a wonderful taste of New Orleans style luncheon at the last minute to accommodate the requests of our seminar hosts. Some of the other reviews here suggest having a courtyard room for quietness--I'd have to agree. I personally don't handle noise well and the noise on the street was overwhelming for me, particularly when I needed rest to take in the information I was there to learn. The noise level is by no means the fault of the hotel, however, and if you are the party type and like to be in the middle of a big party all night long, those street side and balcony rooms are definitely the place for it.If it weren't for our experiences with the front desk staff, I'd probably have rated the hotel above average or excellent. 
