<Author>JimL
<Content>I keep coming back...anyway This is my second review of the B.O. I have stayed there four times in my now ten annual December trips to the Quarter. As someone else posted, it is a three star hotel bordering on four-star -- but mainly for location and appearance, not content and service.Overall I rate it a high 3.5, and I will return, but not necessarily on every trip. THere are many places available with similar discounted rates and facilities. However, if I had to pay their rack rates I would go elsewhere. Their sister, Canal Place, on the edge of the Quarter, is much nicer at just slightly higher prices. It's just farther away.  In low season one can find deep discounts (here as well as elsewhere), which makes it worth putting up with some inconveniences. Location and price. I would personally pay a bit more, and put up with even a few more problems, for the location - but that is my preference. The problems I have experienced are usually minor -- service forgotten or messed up, wrong room assigned, and very inconsistent level of training and performance of staff -- housekeeping, desk, door, maintenance. One reviewer mentioned a concierge -- I haven't seen a concierge at the desk since my first stay six years ago. But I mostly fend for myself, not seeking special attention or services.The recent renovations are nice, and were much needed due to normal wear and tear. The new three connecting bars on the main floor (this seems to be a Wyndham trend in several of their cities) were mostly empty or even closed during the pre-Xmas slow season. I don't see why they felt the need to compete with all the bars and clubs in the Quarter. Their previous small lobby bar, to me, was adequate, and it was never crowded. People don't go to a hotel for nightlife - of that type, anyway. 
