<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>We were treated like royalty We stayed here from May 17th - 20th. The renovations are nearly complete. The Bar area in the lobby is all that's left to be completed. The staff was wonderful to us. We are a Wyndham Card holder, and as promised (if available) they will bump you up. We were to have a deluxe double (two double beds) and were bumped up (for the same price) to a Junior Suite on the 5th floor overlooking Bourbon St. This hotel is GRAND. The new renovations to the beautiful lobby and to the rooms will take your breath away. We never noticed the sounds of Bourbon st up on the 5th floor. We were right across the street from the famous Fritzels Jazz bar - as well as The Funky Pirate where you can hear Big Al Carson and the Blues Masters play (if you go anywhere or do anything - Big Al should be #1 on your list - tell him Linda of the cousins sent you!) Also directly across the street is the Tropical Isle - where you can experience great rock bands and the most powerful drink in New Orleans - the Handgrenade. Jackson Square is two blocks away. Around the corner is the famous Preservation Hall and Pat O'Briens Pub. Shops galore - restaurants galore - and all you want to see and do. You cannot stay at a hotel more centrally located than the Bourbon Orleans - and now that renovations are nearly through - I'm sure you'll be nothing but 100% satisfied with your stay there. I can't wait to go back and I'd never stay at another place. ...and by the way - ...the pool and courtyard surrounding it is just as wonderful as the rest of the hotel. The restaurant is only open for breakfast right now (wonderful food)..but we are told by next year they will be open for breakfast, lunch and dinner. DO stay here - you won't be sorry. 
