<Content>Horrible experience 10/02/03 and Wyndham corp. doesn't care Went to New Orleans for a wedding at the St. Louis Cathedral. Spent 3 nights at the Bourbon Orleans, signed up with the Wyndham rewards program ByRequest. Arrived at the hotel and found the door greeters friendly, nice looking lobby.Front desk confirmed our reservations and told us they were undergoing rennovations. We had booked a townhouse room with a loft and balcony (according to the web desription of the room. Also, as a ByRequest member, had free high speed internet access at no charge). Had to remind desk staff that we we ByRequest members (they said Oh, you sure are.). Got placed in a first floor room, which I thought odd considering it was to have a balcony. Go in the room and yes, it NEEDS renovation, but it is not real bad. Yes, there was a loft for the bedroom. Furniture throughout was quite worn and beat-up. Desk had no chair and of course, the room had no balcony. Asked the front desk for the balcony room as we had reserved. No deal...all full up, no waiting list in case of cancellation. Oh, what about the advertised ByRequest amenities? The front desk personel had that ominous deer caught in the headlights look, uh, they'll be delivered shortly. In other words, never. What time do renovation begin each morning? We are told not until 9:00-9:30. Sounded unusual, but okay. Next morning, we get wakened by the sounds of a drill and a hammer...the paint smell came later....all this at 7:30 a.m., every morning.Ok, let's setup the laptop. Go to the front desk to get the connection cable. They'll have to send one to the room that afternoon. Cable shows up and spend the next hour trying to get the port to work. It's all plugged up, but no juice. The front desk staff has no clue and only an Oh well.The sink in the living area apparantly had a leak, cause the carpet is soaked. We call and tell them of the trouble, somebody will be right over. Late that afternoon, housekeeping arrived to mop up the carpet. The leak was never fixed and requests to move rooms denied.Saturday night ran into a couple at the bar downstairs...the ONE good thing about the hotel was the bartender Layne I believe. (makes a heck of a Bloody Mary). Anyway, we got to talking and come to find out, they had just called the hotel on a lark Friday morning the day before, and received a room with a loft and balcony. Not their fault, but we had been lied to again by the staff.Get home after a fabulous wedding and write a complaint on the Wyndham website about our experience. (Complaining at checkout was met only with a we are under renovation, sorry for your trouble.) Three days later got a corporate response, that Wyndham-Bourbon Orleans was under renovation, they were looking forward to their new wonderful hotel and they were sure everything would be better. They were sorry for our bad experience and they appreciated us staying at Wyndham. That was it. Oh, and they would discuss our issues with the staff. In other words, completely blown off.Stay at a Wyndham at your own risk. They may make assurances of your satisfaction, but absolutely refuse to back these promises up.I have stayed in many hotels and this is the fiorst time I have ever felt compelled to write a negative report or complain to corporate. It is also my first and last time at a Wyndham. If you have any other options...take them while you can and beware of Wyndham non-refundable rates! 
