<Content>Great location; so-so hotel We stayed here 9/17-9/21. I read the reviews going into this so I was not expecting a 5-star hotel. This was my 5th time in New Orleans and my priority on this trip was having a hotel with a central location. That part fully met my expectations as we were close to everything! I've stayed at the Windsor Court before (now *that* is a luxury hotel) but there's something to be said for not having to repeatedly cross Canal Street to/from the French Quarter. I'm not a fussy person or a chronic complainer, so I feel my review of this hotel is not exaggerated. From the outside we first noticed a huge scaffolding on the entire face of the hotel (the part facing Bourbon). It turns out they are just starting a badly needed remodeling project starting on the 6th floor and working their way down. Only on one morning did we notice any construction noise, and they must not have worked on the weekends. The person at the front desk was pleasant and helpful. We had 2 of the multi-level suites booked and only one was ready so we took all of our stuff there. I noticed immediately a musty smell, and the drapes seemed dusty - an allergy sufferer's nightmare. I doubt they had been cleaned for years. The hallways were kind of scary as well. The room was supposed to have a mini-fridge but was not there (ours did had one, however). Our room had drapes but no sheers which might not have been a problem if we hadn't been on the first level. If we wanted any light in the room we had to leave the drapes open, which meant passersby could just look in our room. One guy even stopped and stared at some things on our desk thinking it was a storefront! When he saw us looking back he became startled and quickly left! Our hairdryer was broken and after 2 calls it was replaced. The faucets in the bathroom were needing something...they didn't just drip, they would actually spring back and pour out water full force. They probably want you to think it's part of the hotel charm and blame the tricky faucets on the resident ghosts, but I'm pretty sure the real explanation is much more mundane. The staff seemed friendly and helpful (front desk, concierge, and bellhops/doormen). I know other people have complained about the service, but the major faults I found were with the actual facilities, not the people. I'm not sure if I would stay there again -- it may depend on how well their remodeling project goes! 
