<Content>AVOID AT ALL COSTS! STAY AWAY! LISTEN TO YOUR FELLOW TRAVELERS! I booked this hotel through Priceline.com. I was very surprised to get this hotel for $60. I thought, Wow! What a great location!...and it is a great location...and THAT'S IT. I wouldn't have paid $6 for this hole. The hotel itself is horrible. It is filthy, just like everyone one this board says. I, too, had the exact same problems as everyone else. A/C is inadequate, and there is mold EVERYWHERE (and I don't care how humid it is, or how high the water table is, there's NO excuse for mold and filth. There are plenty of other hotels in N.O. that are in the SAME climate, but they don't have mold. It is a housekeeping issue), dust and hair were all over the place. (I could've started a hair-transplant clinic from the specimens in this room.) The windows are filthy, bathroom had more hair than that of a nest of molting Sasquatch. There are stains on everything, and all you can do is sit in your hot room and wonder what caused them all. I honestly think that housekeeping simply threw the bed back together from the previous guests and closed the door...they certainly could not have cleaned it. Complained to management immediately. Manager's secretary handled the complaint since the front desk was completely apathetic. I, too, was upgraded to the townhouse suite. (I think that they keep several of these suites available for complaining guests after reading everybody else's experiences...it seems to be the standard solution.) The townhouse was on ground level with people walking by all hours. Not a problem except that the curtains didn't close. So much for privacy! (Why go to Bourbon St. for a show when you can walk by and watch the unhappy guests in the complainer's townhouse suite??) This suite was also just as filthy and moldy as the rest of the hotel. After three room changes, sweating to death, and inhaling God-knows-what from the dirt and mold, I demanded my non-refundable payment back, and after screaming and jumping up and down, I got it. I moved to the Place D'Arms and from there completely enjoyed my New Orleans vacation. AVOID THIS HOTEL!! Wyndham has gone downhill big time in the last few years. I will no longer stay with them ever again. They are horrible, with very unhappy employees. 
